[SN]TITLE[SN]
Belfast rioters' legal aid cost £34,000

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The cost of legal aid for people prosecuted for rioting in Belfast in July 2010 has topped £34,000.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Twenty-six men were charged with rioting and related offences during serious disturbances in north Belfast.
All were granted legal aid and all pleaded guilty. The bill could rise when other claims are processed.
The information was released by Justice Minister David Ford in reply to a question by Lord Morrow in the Assembly.
